4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT CREATING THE "DEFEND THE GUARD ACT"; REQUIRING AN
5 OFFICIAL CONGRESSIONAL DECLARATION OR ACTION TO RELEASE THE MONTANA NATIONAL
6 GUARD TO ACTIVE COMBAT DUTY; PROVIDING POWERS OF THE GOVERNOR REGARDING THE
7 MONTANA NATIONAL GUARD; PROVIDING DEFINITIONS; AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE
8 DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Short title. [Sections 1 through 4] may be cited as the "Defend the
13 Guard Act".
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Definitions. As used in [sections 1 through 4], the following definitions
16 apply:
17 (1) "Actions pursuant to Article I, section 8, clause 15" means actions explicitly taken by the United
18 States congress to call forth the militia to:
19 (a) execute the laws of the United States;
20 (b) suppress insurrections; or
21 (c) repel invasions.
22 (2) "Active duty combat" means performing one or more of the following services in the active
23 federal military of the United States:
24 (a) participation in an armed conflict;
25 (b) performance of a hazardous service relating to an armed conflict in a foreign state; or
26 (c) performance of a duty through an instrumentality of war.
27 (3) "Instrumentality of war" means any tool, equipment, technology, or personnel, including
28 Montana national guard personnel, specifically employed in support of or directly engaged in armed conflict or
- 1 - LC 892

