1 military operations, including noncombat-related support elements.
2 (4) "Official declaration of war" means an official declaration of war made by the United States
3 congress pursuant to Article I, section 8, clause 11, of the United States constitution.
4
5 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Montana national guard -- official declaration or official action
6 required. (1) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, the Montana national guard and any member of the
7 Montana national guard may not be released from the state into federal duty, including active duty combat,
8 unless the United States congress has:
9 (a) passed an official declaration of war; or
10 (b) taken an official action pursuant to Article I, section 8, clause 15, of the United States
11 constitution to explicitly call forth the Montana national guard or any member of the Montana national guard for
12 any of the purposes enumerated in that clause.
13 (2) The governor shall take any action necessary to enforce this section.
14
15 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Governor's powers. (1) Nothing in [sections 1 through 4] limits or
16 restricts the governor's authority under Title 32 of the United States Code to consent to the activation of the
17 Montana national guard for federally funded missions that remain under state control, including but not limited
18 to:
19 (a) training and readiness within the United States or its territories or in friendly foreign countries;
20 (b) responding to domestic emergencies, including natural disasters and public health crises;
21 (c) homeland defense activities to protect public safety and critical infrastructure;
22 (d) counter-drug operations within the United States or its territories; and
23 (e) other authorized missions consistent with Title 32 of the United States Code.
24 (2) Nothing in [sections 1 through 4] prohibits any constitutionally authorized mission conducted
25 under Title 10 of the United States Code, provided that the mission does not violate the provisions of [sections
26 1 through 4].
27
